JWT_SECRET`).\n   - JWT middleware validates token, extracts `userId`, `tenantId`, `role` and attaches to `req.user`.\n   - Profile route returns user info.\n   - Role‑based helper to check admin for role changes.\n4. **Event Ingestion**:\n   - POST `/events` for single event, body includes `name, properties?, timestamp?`.\n   - POST `/events/batch` accepting array of events.\n   - Insert into `events` with generated UUID, tenant_id from `req.user.tenantId`.\n5. **Query Engine**:\n   - GET `/events/count?name=...` → count rows matching filter for tenant.\n   - GET `/events/timeseries?name=...&interval=day` → group by date bucket.\n   - GET `/events/breakdown?name=...&property=...` → GROUP BY JSON property value (use SQLite JSON functions).\n6. **Dashboard CRUD**:\n   - Standard REST (`/dashboards`) with tenant scoping.\n   - Use UUID ids.\n   - Owner check for update/delete.\n7. **Export**:\n   - GET `/export/events?format=csv|json` → stream data.\n   - GET `/export/dashboards?format=csv|json`.\n   - Ensure tenant filter.\n8. **App Factory**: Implement `createApp` in `src/index.ts` that sets up Express, middleware, routes, DB init.\n9. **Lint/Tests**:\n   - Ensure code passes `npm run lint`.\n   - Write vitest + supertest tests covering auth, event ingestion, count query, dashboard CRUD.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/index.ts` – app factory\n- `src/db.ts` – SQLite connection & schema init\n- `src/middleware/auth.ts` – JWT verification\n- `src/routes/auth.ts` – register, login, profile, role change\n- `src/routes/events.ts` – ingestion & queries\n- `src/routes/dashboards.ts` – CRUD\n- `src/routes/export.ts` – export endpoints\n- `src/utils/uuid.ts` – wrapper around `uuid/v4`\n- `src/types.ts` – shared TypeScript interfaces\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Password hashing library**: `bcrypt` not listed; fallback to `crypto.pbkdf2Sync`.\n- **JWT secret**: Require `.env` with `JWT_SECRET`; create placeholder if missing.\n- **SQLite JSON queries**: Ensure `better-sqlite3` supports JSON functions (SQLite 3.38+). Use `json_extract`.\n- **Testing async DB**: Use fresh in‑memory SQLite for tests.\n- **Export streaming**: For simplicity, generate full string and send; acceptable for benchmark size.\n\n## Next Steps\nCreate the project structure and DB init (Task 1).","encoding":"utf-8"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772754797650,"end":1772754797658}}}}
